{
  "text": "There is a lot of research that aims at mitigating the undesirable PCM characteristics. As mentioned above, buffer organizations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] are effective to hide the impacts of slow PCM writes (compared to DRAM). Write cancellation and write pausing [CITATION_5] improves the performance of PCM reads by delaying the extremely slow write operations.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "14498175",
